      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "import sys\n\ndef bwt(s):\n    # Table of rotations of string\n    table = sorted(s[i:] + s[:i] for i in range(len(s)))\n\n    print(*table, sep='\\n', file=sys.stderr)\n    print('-----', file=sys.stderr)\n\n    # Last characters of each row\n    last_column = [row[-1] for row in table] \n\n    return str(1 + table.index(s)) + ''.join(last_column)\n\ns = input()\nprint(bwt(s))",
      "statement": "Compute the Burrows-Wheeler transform of the given string. The algorithm is as follows:\n\nGiven a string, say [[BAHAMAS]], compute the list of all cyclic rotations of the string:\n\n<<B>>AHAMAS\nS<<B>>AHAMA\nAS<<B>>AHAM\nMAS<<B>>AHA\nAMAS<<B>>AH\nHAMAS<<B>>A\nAHAMAS<<B>>\n\nSort this list of strings lexicographically, and the result is the string made of the last characters of each line, preceded by the position of the original text in this sorted list:\n\nAHAMAS<<B>>    1\nAMASBA<<H>>    2\nASBAHA<<M>>    3\nBAHAMA<<S>>    4    <-- original text\nHAMASB<<A>>    5\nMASBAH<<A>>    6\nSBAHAM<<A>>    7\n\nThe result is therefore [[4BHMSAAA]].",
